13/02/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The new union of the merged Croatian Social Liberal Party and Liberal Party -- to be referred to as HSLS -- held its first session Saturday (11 February).
Delegates unanimously elected Djurdja Adlesic as leader.
She later told the state-run TV HRT that for the time being, HSLS plans to remain a partner of the ruling Croatian Democratic Union, adding that HSLS's main goal is to win 10 per cent to 15 per cent of votes in the next parliamentary elections.
(HRT - 11/02/06)
